The paper discusses the security and privacy threats associated with cyber physical systems (CPSs) and presents differential privacy as an efficient technique to protect CPSs data privacy. This indicates that the paper is likely to belong to the categories of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.CY (Computers and Society), and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also discusses the application and implementation of differential privacy in various CPSs applications such as energy systems, transportation systems, healthcare and medical systems, and industrial Internet of things (IIoT), which suggests that the paper may also belong to the categories of cs.DB (Databases) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
